==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official architectural principles of the NEXOTFE ERP.

These principles are mandatory.

Every technical decision must comply with them.

If a proposed solution violates any principle described here, the solution must be rejected.

==========================================================
BUSINESS FIRST
==========================================================

Every implementation begins with the business.

Never begin with:

• Database

• Backend

• Frontend

• Technology

The correct sequence is always:

Business Process

↓

Business Rules

↓

Business Entities

↓

Database

↓

Backend

↓

Frontend

↓

Optimization

==========================================================
DATABASE PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

The database represents the business.

It does not represent:

Pages.

Screens.

Components.

React structure.

Frontend layout.

Every table must exist because a real business entity exists.

==========================================================
MODULE PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

NEXOTFE is composed of independent business modules.

Examples:

Customers

Suppliers

Employees

Products

Raw Materials

Projects

Purchasing

Routing

Quotations

Commercial Proposals

Modules may communicate.

Modules must not become unnecessarily dependent.

==========================================================
BUSINESS OWNERSHIP
==========================================================

Business modules own database tables.

Database tables never define business modules.

The business always comes first.

==========================================================
SIMPLICITY
==========================================================

Prefer the simplest solution that correctly represents the business.

Avoid unnecessary abstractions.

Avoid unnecessary layers.

Avoid duplicated information.

Avoid unnecessary configuration.

==========================================================
LONG-TERM THINKING
==========================================================

Every implementation must consider long-term maintenance.

Temporary solutions should be avoided.

Architecture must survive future expansion.

==========================================================
APPROVED DECISIONS
==========================================================

Previously approved business decisions are permanent.

Never redesign approved concepts.

Never replace approved architecture without explicit authorization.

Evolution means extending the approved architecture.

It never means recreating it.

==========================================================
DATABASE MODIFICATIONS
==========================================================

Database changes require explicit approval.

Never modify Supabase automatically.

Never rename tables without approval.

Never rename fields without approval.

Never remove business information without approval.

==========================================================
FRONT-END PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

The Front-End exists to represent the business.

It must be:

Simple.

Consistent.

Professional.

Fast.

Predictable.

The user interface must never introduce unnecessary complexity.

==========================================================
USER EXPERIENCE
==========================================================

Every screen must help users make faster and better business decisions.

Visual beauty is important.

Productivity is mandatory.

Whenever there is a conflict between aesthetics and productivity,

productivity wins.

==========================================================
IMPLEMENTATION PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

Work one module at a time.

Finish it.

Test it.

Approve it.

Freeze it.

Then continue with the next module.

Avoid parallel implementation of multiple modules.

==========================================================
ENGINEERING STANDARD
==========================================================

Every implementation must improve at least one of the following:

Business value.

Maintainability.

Performance.

Security.

Consistency.

User productivity.

If none of these improves,

the implementation should be reconsidered.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

The objective of NEXOTFE is not to create software.

The objective is to create an engineering platform that faithfully represents the operation of a modern industrial company.

Every architectural decision must reinforce this objective.